The paper deals with graph-theoretic characterizations of tree compatibility, which is a problem in phylogenetics. The paper uses concepts from graph theory such as triangulation, chordal graphs, and minimal cuts. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
